<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Alexander Zverev came back from the brink of another Grand Slam failure on Friday night as he outlasted Pablo Carreno Busta in five sets at Flushing Meadows.</p>

<p>The German No 5 seed found himself two sets down to the Spaniard but launched  spirited fightback to prevail 3-6, 2-6, 6-3, 6-4, 6-3.</p>

<p>More to follow </p>

<p>Alexander Zverev has reached his first ever Grand Slam final at this year's US Open</p>

<p>Spaniard Pablo Carreno Busta required medical attention ahead of the fifth and final set</p>

<p>Carreno Busta had sailed into a two-set lead as Zverev once again struggled on the big stage</p>

<p>The German fifth seed looked visibly frustrated as he collapsed in the opening exchanges</p>
